content.How to Contribute: Thank you for considering contributing to Hypothetical Repo! Contributions help us grow and improve, and we appreciate your interest. Please go through [Readme](./README.md) to get the project overview or you can make doc changes here [Docs](https://github.com/Prashant528/ideal_documented_repo/tree/main/docs).
content.Reporting Bugs: - **Report Bugs**: Found a bug? Create an issue with details such as steps to reproduce, expected behavior, and any relevant screenshots or logs.
content.Submitting Enhancements: - **Submit Enhancements**: Have a feature idea? Propose it in an issue. Be sure to explain the problem it solves and how it improves the project. Also, don't forget to look at the [template](https://github.com/Prashant528/ideal_documented_repo/blob/main/templates/template_1/readme.md) for a feature request.
content.Pull Requests: - **Pull Requests**: Review the guidelines for submitting your changes. Ensure your code is well-documented and adheres to our style guidelines.
content.Setup Guide:
To set up the project locally:
- Follow the [Installation Guide](./INSTALLATION_GUIDE.md) to install dependencies and set up your environment.
- Make your changes and test locally to ensure they work as intended.
- Submit your pull request with a detailed description of your changes.
